text: Jupiter Playground has amazing facilities. It has tunnels, slides, a climbing area, a mini slide, music bells and even an exercising corner.

Neat little neighbourhood playground. Equipment is nearly brand new, clearly recently revamped. There’s an open space for badminton, and some exercise equipment as well for the elderly. Clearly meant to serve residents living nearby, but if you’re nearby and need a place to exercise the kids, why not.

Love the design and architect of the playground. There are 4 slides with good shades, musical bells, obstacles climbers etc. The place is sounded with trees (providing shades) and seats for parents. Near Venus trail. Great place for walks and play.

Lovely, clean playground for kids. Lots of benches for parents to sit and watch their kids. Quite near Venus Walk if you are coming from Windsor Nature Park, good for a nature + playtime combo for young kids

Quite new and very nice playground. Offers different climbing obstacles for every age. There are also some benches under a roof for rainy days. You can access the Venus Walk at the end of the Windsor Park Rd to combine it with a hiking trip.
